 nniversary
DESCRIPTION:A letter by Dutch official Pieter Schaghen\, dated Nov. 5\, 1
 626\, reported that colonists had 'purchased' the island of Manhattan fr
 om its Native inhabitants for goods worth 60 guilders. It is the only co
 ntemporary document of the transaction.\n\nhttps://www.newnetherlandinst
 itute.org/history-and-heritage/additional-resources/dutch-treats/peter-s
 chaghen-letter/
